g.text: Minha Casa, Minha Vida builds new
construction on vacant land for the purpose
of affordable housing.
Morar Carioca, an evolution of Favela
Bairro, is promoted as part of the Olympic
Plan for Rio de Janeiro. Morar Carioca
pledged to integrate every favela into the
formal city by the year 2020.
Unidade de Polícia Pacificadora is a state
law enforcement that reclaims territories
from control of gangs and drug dealers.
Known as PAC, Program de Aceleração do
Crescimento is an initiative to upgrade
infrastructural projects in the public realm
of the City.
Favela-Bairro was a physical upgrading
program that aimed to integrate slums into
the fabric of the formal city, by providing
access to basic urban and social services,
as well as assisting in the regularization of
public and private spaces within the
favela.
